The paper discusses the use of deep recurrent neural networks for generating goal-directed plans for a real arm robot based on prior learning experience. This involves extracting a predictive model from visuomotor experiences related to object-directed behaviors. The paper also discusses the error minimization principle in the predictive coding framework and the need for sufficient generalization through a large number of learning trajectories. Based on these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is robotics (cs.RO), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
